Project-based internship will concentrate on design and implementation of the real project based on initial task provided by a particular organization. Within the internships students in cooperation with the internship organization are required to determine the scope and outcomes of the project, design a plan for project realization and implement it. They are also required to compile a final report of the project and defend it in the commission including representatives of internship organization and the faculty.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the internship is to provide opportunity for students to apply the knowledge and skills acquired during the studies to design, implement and evaluate real information management project in organization.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On completion of the course, students: - have basic knowledge about project management; - can determine and critically evaluate the needs and resources of the organization concerning information management; - are able to plan and implement actions related to the initial task proposed by the organization; - are able to apply knowledge and skills acquired during the studies in information management practice; - have necessary negotiation and teamwork skills.
